oai_dc:dc.dc:title: Duration of Immunity Induced by Commercially Available Pasteurella haemolytica Vaccines
oai_dc:dc.dc:creator: Loan, Raymond W.
Tung, Hsi-tang
Payne, Jerry B.
oai_dc:dc.dc:subject: Pasteurella haemolytica
vaccines
immunity studies
Immunity
oai_dc:dc.dc:description: Calves on range with their dams were vaccinated with 5 commercially available Pasteurella haemolytica vaccines in duration of immunity studies. Immunity was challenged at 83 and 97 days post-vaccination by transthoracic inoculation of virulent P haemolytica.
